atter how good your anti-spam measures, some will get past. This add-on logs spam form submissions via <b>WP fail2ban</b>, and provides a new filter for <i>fail2ban</i>.</p>\n<p><b>N.B.</b> This add-on provides support for Contact Form 7; it does not include it, nor is it affiliated in any way.</p>\";s:17:\"short_description\";s:59:\"Integration with Contact Form 7: log spam form submissions.\";s:10:\"banner_url\";s:61:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/3564/banner.png\";s:15:\"card_banner_url\";s:66:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/3564/card_banner.png\";s:15:\"selling_point_0\";N;s:15:\"selling_point_1\";N;s:15:\"selling_point_2\";N;s:11:\"screenshots\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:3:\"751\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2020-06-17 18:28:20\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2019-04-01 16:45:54\";s:22:\"\0FS_Entity\0_is_updated\";b:0;}s:10:\"is_premium\";b:0;s:14:\"premium_suffix\";s:9:\"(Premium)\";s:7:\"is_live\";b:1;s:9:\"bundle_id\";N;s:17:\"bundle_public_key\";N;s:10:\"public_key\";s:32:\"pk_7e0e413b0ffb7551b21cf57501455\";s:10:\"secret_key\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"3564\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2022-04-08 00:57:09\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2019-04-01 16:27:41\";s:22:\"\0FS_Entity\0_is_updated\";b:0;}i:1;O:9:\"FS_Plugin\":23:{s:16:\"parent_plugin_id\";s:4:\"3072\";s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Gravity Forms\";s:4:\"slug\";s:31:\"wp-fail2ban-addon-gravity-forms\";s:12:\"premium_slug\";s:39:\"wp-fail2ban-addon-gravity-forms-premium\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"plugin\";s:20:\"affiliate_moderation\";N;s:19:\"is_wp_org_compliant\";b:1;s:22:\"premium_releases_count\";i:0;s:4:\"file\";N;s:7:\"version\";N;s:11:\"auto_update\";N;s:4:\"info\";O:14:\"FS_Plugin_Info\":13:{s:9:\"plugin_id\";s:4:\"3565\";s:11:\"description\";s:180:\"<p>No matter how good your anti-spam measures, some will get past. This add-on logs spam form submissions via <b>WP fail2ban</b>, and provides a new filter for <i>fail2ban</i>.</p>\";s:17:\"short_description\";s:58:\"Integration with Gravity Forms: log spam form submissions.\";s:10:\"banner_url\";s:61:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/3565/banner.png\";s:15:\"card_banner_url\";s:66:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/3565/card_banner.png\";s:15:\"selling_point_0\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"selling_point_1\";N;s:15:\"selling_point_2\";N;s:11:\"screenshots\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:3:\"752\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2019-04-10 07:48:36\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2019-04-01 17:49:23\";s:22:\"\0FS_Entity\0_is_updated\";b:0;}s:10:\"is_premium\";b:0;s:14:\"premium_suffix\";s:9:\"(Premium)\";s:7:\"is_live\";b:1;s:9:\"bundle_id\";N;s:17:\"bundle_public_key\";N;s:10:\"public_key\";s:32:\"pk_8c5d4d69296f78a9827a02d66732b\";s:10:\"secret_key\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"3565\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2022-03-22 05:47:38\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2019-04-01 17:45:47\";s:22:\"\0FS_Entity\0_is_updated\";b:0;}i:2;O:9:\"FS_Plugin\":23:{s:16:\"parent_plugin_id\";s:4:\"3072\";s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"WP fail2ban Blocklist\";s:4:\"slug\";s:21:\"wpf2b-addon-blocklist\";s:12:\"premium_slug\";s:35:\"wp-fail2ban-addon-blocklist-premium\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"plugin\";s:20:\"affiliate_moderation\";N;s:19:\"is_wp_org_compliant\";b:1;s:22:\"premium_releases_count\";i:11;s:4:\"file\";N;s:7:\"version\";N;s:11:\"auto_update\";N;s:4:\"info\";O:14:\"FS_Plugin_Info\":13:{s:9:\"plugin_id\";s:4:\"6750\";s:11:\"description\";s:1071:\"<p>There are many plugins that use a database to check for malicious IPs <b>after</b> they connect, and of course <tt>fail2ban</tt> stops <i>repeated</i> attacks, but what if bad IPs could be blocked <b>before</b> they connect?</p>\n<p>By working collaboratively - sharing attack data - <i>WP fail2ban Blocklist</i> does exactly that.</p>\n<h3>How</h3>\n<p>The Blocklist Network Service (BNS) collects attack data from participating sites, performs some analytical magic, and sends back a list of IPs that are attacking sites now but haven\'t yet attacked that site.</p>\n<p>In other words, each site regularly gets a unique list of IPs to block <b>preemptively</b>.</p>\n<h3>GDPR</h3>\n<p>The BNS doesn\'t collect personal data, and bots don\'t have rights.</p>\n<p>That said, the BNS only collects the minimum data required (time, IP, event), and only for IPs that have behaved maliciously.</p>\n<p>Of course, it is possible that some data is generated by <i>people</i> behaving maliciously, but the BNS has no way to differentiate - and nor should it: an attack is an attack.</p>\";s:17:\"short_description\";s:58:\"A <b>preemptive collaborative blocklist</b> for WordPress.\";s:10:\"banner_url\";s:61:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/6750/banner.png\";s:15:\"card_banner_url\";s:66:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/6750/card_banner.png\";s:15:\"selling_point_0\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"selling_point_1\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"selling_point_2\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"screenshots\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"1811\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2021-06-19 07:49:45\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2020-09-17 00:17:38\";s:22:\"\0FS_Entity\0_is_updated\";b:0;}s:10:\"is_premium\";b:0;s:14:\"premium_suffix\";s:9:\"(Premium)\";s:7:\"is_live\";b:1;s:9:\"bundle_id\";N;s:17:\"bundle_public_key\";N;s:10:\"public_key\";s:32:\"pk_02a7118d5d6b8dddbf72b18fb0f19\";s:10:\"secret_key\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"6750\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2022-04-07 15:17:49\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2020-08-16 15:43:46\";s:22:\"\0FS_Entity\0_is_updated\";b:0;}}}}','yes'),(152,'fs_gdpr','a:1:{s:2:\"u1\";a:1:{s:8:\"required\";b:0;}}','yes'),(153,'fs_api_cache','a:1:{s:55:\"get:/v1/plugins/3072/addons.json?enriched=true&count=50\";O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:6:\"result\";O:8:\"stdClass\":1:{s:7:\"plugins\";a:3:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":33:{s:16:\"parent_plugin_id\";s:4:\"3072\";s:12:\"developer_id\";s:4:\"3751\";s:8:\"store_id\";s:4:\"1269\";s:10:\"install_id\";s:7:\"2540194\";s:4:\"slug\";s:32:\"wp-fail2ban-addon-contact-form-7\";s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Contact Form 7\";s:11:\"environment\";i:0;s:4:\"icon\";s:93:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/3564/icons/a3ec38d117446af49003e296b